			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Plastics are persistent large-scale pollutants, and plastic debris and particulates have been found in many environmental niches. The production and disposal of plastic generates greenhouse gases and hazardous waste. Plastic and the chemicals it emits are building up on land and in oceans, lakes, rivers, ice, and air. They are tiny shards of plastic measuring up to 5mm in length. In 2018 more than 343 million tonnes of plastic waste were generated, 90% of which was composed of post-consumer plastic waste.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">塑料是一种持久性大规模污染物，在许多环境壁龛中都发现了塑料碎片和微粒。塑料的生产和处理会产生温室气体和有害废物。塑料及其释放的化学物质在陆地、海洋、湖泊、河流、冰层和空气中不断积累。它们是长达 5 毫米的细小塑料碎片。2018 年产生的塑料垃圾超过 3.43 亿吨，其中 90% 是消费后塑料垃圾。</common:generalComment>
